post.title: Our story
post.excerpt: Our journey starts a long time ago, in 2004, with a company called MoIP (Money over IP). One of our founders, Leo, was visiting Silicon Valley and he came across the Paypal business model, which was disrupting US traditional payment methods at that time.
post.content:
When he came back to Brazil, he immediately went over to Igor with an idea: “we have to create a similar business in Brazil”. Long story short, MoIP was a huge success and, in 2016, they sold the business to Wirecard for US$41MM. MoIP started with the aspiration to be the Brazilian Paypal, but, when it started to scale, its purpose became helping SME company owners to thrive in their businesses. MoIP supported hundreds of thousands of business owners to receive online payments and walk their first steps into the digital universe, watching them grow inside MoIP’s platform. As they were helping other small entrepreneurs to succeed, Leo and Igor fastly understood the economic impact of small business and it led them to find their life’s purpose, which was to develop solutions that could help those entrepreneurs.

In this MoIP journey, the founders learned a lot in terms of scaling a company, hiring people, setting up a good business strategy and raising money, but more importantly, it showed them what they love to do and what they don’t want to do. The founders became part of the Wirecard executive team until the end of 2018 when Wirecard changed its MoIP focus to enterprises instead of SMBs, and Leo and Igor knew that wasn’t what they want to do and they decided to leave Wirecard to create more solutions to the SMBs. This was the first Cora’s call for an adventure.

When they left Wirecard they had this weird sensation that there was still a lot to do in the Brazilian financial system but payments were no more an issue for the SMBs. The industry in need of disruption was banking. We started Cora to provide a superior offering to Brazilian consumers. When we launched Cora, as is the case today, incumbent banks in Latin America offered similar checking account products, credit limits, interest rates, and annual fees to all customers based on homogenous underwriting methodologies and customer management strategies. We believed that customers in Brazil were paying some of the highest interest rates and fees in the world, and were often ignored and taken for granted. There are 6.4 million businesses in Brazil, and 99% of them are small enterprises, accounting for 52% of formal jobs in the private sector (16.1 million) – according to Sebrae¹ (a Brazilian organization supporting SMBs).

Millions of entrepreneurs haven’t received a lot of attention from the large incumbent banks and they frequently have difficulty getting loans and finding financial services tailored to their needs. The 5 biggest traditional banks in Brazil hold approximately 70% of the total credit offers operations - according to the Brazilian Central Bank (2019) - and their biggest profits come from expensive credit lines offered to SME businesses, resulting in a 42% net margin on their top 3 credit products. Even though those rates are no good, SME business owners have to choose them only because they still don’t have enough other options to choose from.

From the beginning, our objective has been to solve the difficulties of managing the finances of small and medium-sized companies, creating a completely new service and a simple product, capable of simplifying the routine of the business owners. Looking into the future, we want to be the informed decision making interface of the entrepreneurs.

We know that every business carries a story and that behind this story is someone's persistence and effort. We know this because we are a bank of entrepreneurs. Made with affection, respect and admiration for those who dedicate themselves. Who struggle in their routines to break through an increasingly difficult world on their own.

We are a different bank, which knows how difficult it is to start a business. That's why we don't want to grow for the sake of growing, at any cost. We are a movement. That grows as our customers do. Along with every small business, and the people behind it. More than a bank, a conviction. More than a service, support for your business. Because we know how important it is to you. And how much needs to be done.
